I visited yesterday. There were two Hispanic workers were cutting the ingredients by hand WITHOUT sanitized gloves and they did not wear the mask. I was able to see all this because, they opened the kitchen wide open. I asked to owner, why they did not wear any sanitized globes. She was just saying that she was ensure their hands were cleaned before they came back to work. I was not comfortable, because all these COVID 19,and asked for money back. Hope this place fix this matter

it was worst taste ever I tried on abalone porridge. It came with only white rice and little piece of abalone . Better try with one that korean mart where selling.....Paid $6.99 .... this is real bonjuk.... Dont ever try this ....
Overpriced Korean juk that tastes average at best. Very small portion size and their side dish so tiny it makes me feel like I'm Gulliver.

(Translated by Google) It's a place I visit whenever I get sick, but the porridge is really delicious and clean! The boss is friendly and the store is clean. Personally, beef mushroom porridge is the most delicious, and the side dish that comes with it is also easy to eat with porridge. Highly recommend this place, nice service and clean restaurant. I personally recommend Beef Mushroom Porridge if you like mushrooms. Side dishes are tasty as well. Great korean restaurant.  Very clean and no MSG is used.  Very health conscience.   But it does come with the price.  Lunch would easily cost over 15 per person.  For 3, the lunch would cost over $50.  Not an affordable place.  A great place to go when a company pays.
